Questo 1- A janela de Kaiser criada com 101 coeficientes e frequncia de corte de 3000 Hz que corresponde parte inferior do espectograma.

In [34]:
import math
from scipy import signal

fc = 3000
wc =  (math.pi * fc)/(fs/2)
M = 101
M1 = -(M)/2
M2 = (M)/2
nm = np.arange(M1,M2)

nw = np.arange(M)
r = 100 #Atenuao em DBs
beta = 0.1102*(r- 8.7)

k = (wc/math.pi)*(np.sin(wc*nm)/(wc*nm))
k[nm == 0] = wc/math.pi

kaiser = np.kaiser(M,beta)
k2 = k * kaiser


plt.figure(figsize = (8, 6))
plt.plot(nw, k)
plt.title('Windowed Impulse Response')
plt.xlabel('Samples')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')


plt.figure(figsize = (8, 6))
plt.plot(nw, k2)
plt.title('Kaiser Windowed Impulse Response')
plt.xlabel('Samples')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')

Aps criar o filtro Low-Pass, o sinal deve ser filtrado, removendo as componentes de alta frequncia.

In [61]:
sinalLP = scipy.signal.lfilter(k2,1,wav)

plt.figure(figsize = (20, 6))
plt.plot(T, sinalLP)
plt.xlim(xmin=0,xmax=5)
plt.xticks( np.arange(0,5.5,0.5) )
plt.title('Low-Pass Filtered Signal')
plt.xlabel('Time(s)')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')


############################################################

def plot_spec(Y, fs):
  plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
  ff, tt, sxx = scipy.signal.spectrogram(Y,fs,scaling='spectrum')
  sxx = np.log(sxx)
  plt.pcolormesh(tt, ff, abs(sxx), shading='gouraud')
  plt.ylabel('Frequency [Hz]')
  plt.xlabel('Time [sec]')
  plt.show()

plot_spec(sinalLP,fs)

Questo 2- A partir do filtro Low-Pass possvel criar um filtro High-Pass, que mantm as componentes de alta-frequncia. Este filtro aplicado ao sinal para obter apenas a parte superior do espectograma.

In [62]:
max_value = np.amax(k2)
pos_M = np.where(k2 == max_value)
b_impulse = np.zeros(M)
b_impulse[pos_M] = 1
b_HP = b_impulse - k2

sinalHP = scipy.signal.lfilter(b_HP,1,wav)

plt.figure(figsize = (20, 6))
plt.plot(T, sinalHP)
plt.xlim(xmin=0,xmax=5)
plt.xticks( np.arange(0,5.5,0.5) )
plt.title('High-Pass Filtered Signal')
plt.xlabel('Time(s)')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')

plot_spec(sinalHP,fs)

Questo 2- b) possvel obter um filtro High-Pass a partir dos coeficientes de um filtro Low-Pass atravs de da subtrao deste por um filtro All-Pass, que permite que todo o sinal passe, representado pelo impulso unitrio. Deste modo, a subtrao dos dois componentes resultara na permanncia apenas das componentes de alta frequncia, assim dando forma a um filtro High-Pass.
